    {
        ", with an atomic number of 87. It was then referred to by the provisional name  eka-caesium .   Adloff, Jean-Pierre; Kaufman, George B. .   . The Chemical Educator 10 . Retrieved on 2007-03-26.   Research teams attempted to locate and isolate this missing element, and at least four false claims were made that the element had been found before an authentic discovery was made.       Soviet chemist ": null
