        " in 1995.  Depending on the energy of the oxygen beam, the reaction can yield francium isotopes with masses of 209, 210, and 211.     : 197 Au + 18 O → 209 Fr + 6 n   : 197 Au + 18 O → 210 Fr + 5 n   : 197 Au + 18 O → 211 Fr + 4 n     The francium atoms leave the gold target as ions, which are neutralized by collision with yttrium and then isolated in a ": null
